President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Jennifer L. Fain as Inspector General for the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC). Fain has over 22 years of experience in the Inspector General Community and has served as Deputy Inspector General for the Export-Import Bank of the United States. She has extensive oversight experience in financial services and consumer protection.

Additionally, Christopher Henry Schroeder has been nominated to be a Member of the Board of Trustees of the James Madison Memorial Fellowship Foundation. Schroeder is a law professor and has previously served as Assistant Attorney General for the Office of Legal Counsel in the United States Department of Justice. He has written on various topics in constitutional law and has a background in Congressional procedures and affairs.

Lastly, Daryle Williams has been nominated to be a Member of the National Council on the Humanities. Williams is currently the Dean of the College of Humanities, Arts, and Social Sciences at the University of California, Riverside. He specializes in Latin American history, particularly modern Brazil, and is involved in digital slavery studies. Williams has a strong commitment to educational opportunity and knowledge production in the humanities.

These nominations reflect President Biden's choices for key leadership roles in his administration.